[[File:Halaq at Masjid al-Haram, 6 April 2015, Makkah, Saudi Arabia.jpg|thumb|right|A halaqa is underway inside the main complex of [[Masjid al-Haram]] in [[Makkah]], [[Saudi Arabia]].]] A '''halaqa''' ({{lang-ar|حلقة}} - 'circle / ring') in [[Islamic terminology]] is a religious gathering or meeting for the study of [[Islam]] and the [[Quran]]. Generally, there are one or more primary speakers that present the designated topic(s) of the halaqa while others sit around them (in an approximate circle) and listen. The attendees may participate in the discussions, ask questions, and voice concerns. Usually, prayers and supplications are part of such programs. Also, meals or snacks may be served to the participants.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://sfbasic.org/site/halaqas/index.php |title = The Islamic Halaqas Program |publisher = SF*BASIC |year = 2004}}</ref>
